Jenna Etheridge The accident on the N2. (Supplied) Multimedia    ·   User Galleries   ·   News in Pictures
	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Three people have died and 15 others were seriously injured after the driver of a minibus-taxi lost control on the N2 highway, near the Cape Town International Airport, on Sunday afternoon. Western Cape traffic chief Kenny Africa said the crash happened at the R300 turnoff, in the direction of Cape Town. The on-ramp to the R300 was closed and traffic was backed up. Bystanders could be seen looking down at the accident scene from the bridge overhead. Traffic, medical and law enforcement officials were on scene. The roadway was eventually cleared and re-opened for vehicles at 16:15. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  